  "prompt": "What is  EDNOS? What are some examples?",
  "response": "EDNOS stands for Eating Disorder Not Otherwise Specified, which was a diagnostic category in the DSM-IV (Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 4th edition). In the current DSM-5, it has been replaced with OSFED (Other Specified Feeding or Eating Disorder).\n\nExamples of EDNOS/OSFED include:\n\n1. Atypical Anorexia Nervosa\n- Meets all anorexia criteria except being underweight\n- Significant weight loss and restrictive eating patterns\n- Normal or above-normal body weight\n\n2. Bulimia Nervosa (low frequency/limited duration)\n- Meets most bulimia criteria\n- Binge eating and compensatory behaviors occur less frequently\n\n3. Purging Disorder\n- Regular purging behaviors\n- Without recurring binge eating episodes\n- Can involve self-induced vomiting, laxative or diuretic misuse\n\n4. Night Eating Syndrome\n- Consuming large amounts of food after evening meal\n- Significant nighttime eating\n- Awareness of nighttime eating\n\n5. Binge Eating Disorder (before it became its own diagnosis)\n- Recurring binge eating episodes\n- No regular compensatory behaviors\n- Feelings of shame or distress about eating\n\nThese disorders are serious and can have significant physical and psychological impacts.",
